Knox Wire will host top executives of Nigeria’s leading banks and financial institutions as it unveils its Real Time Gross Settlement (RTGS) services into the market. The country Representative, Sweetapple Capital, Bode Akinboye, said the event would be followed by a conference at the Federal Palace Hotel, Lagos. Knox Wire RTGS  platform has rich  features such as its unparalleled speed during e-payments.   NIN-SIM linkage: Queues continue at enrolment centres,…     Zenith Bank gives N93.33b dividends     CBN fines four banks over crypto transactions   The payment company offers financial institutions real-time to  cross-border payments to a global network of almost 30,000 institutions in 120 countries and 80 currencies. In a statement, the company will be joined by a partner who has opened communication to select financial institutions across  Nigeria. Knox Wire is one of only three major global RTGS solutions but greatly improves upon current offerings by leveraging a correspondent network for off network payments, advanced technical features to provide near-instantaneous cross-border transactions, anti-money laundering transaction monitoring to prevent fraud, and a system that integrates with financial systems. Nigeria’s population and economic base  makes it  important in connecting Knox Wire’s RTGS network to African-based financial institutions.